h=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Level for dragon raids?</span><hr size=1> Hi all... just a quick question.. what is a good level to start signing up for dragon raids? <p><P><center><table border="5" width="75%" bgcolor="#000000" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> 
<tr> 
<td width="35%" align="center"> 
<a href="http://fp.geocities.com/blood_inferno"> 
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://fp.geocities.com/blood_inferno/images/BILogo6.jpg" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=75></td></a> 
<td width="55%" align="center"> 
<p align="center"><font face="Script MT Bold" color="#CC0000" size="6"><b>Ectasy</b></font></p> 
<p align="center"><font face="Arial" color="#CC0000" size="2">Druid of the 45th Season</font></p></td> <td width="5%" align="center"> 
<a href="http://sr.amiga.tm/brell/players.cgi?view=0114"> 
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://fp.geocities.com/blood_inferno/images/druid.jpg" WIDTH=35 HEIGHT=75></td></a> 
</tr> 
</table></center></p> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uauelanlifebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Auelan Lifebringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/14/01 6:12:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level for dragon raids?</span><hr size=1> If you mean nag/vox, I dunno...mid/high 40's maybe? I'd say 47-48 would be about the lowest unless you're a vital class. A lot depends on resist gear as well. Try to get your respective cold/fire resists up to 180-220 or so (I still think there is a cap, irregardless of what Ester says).<br>
<br>
Auelan Lifebringer<br>
57th season Templar of Tunare<br>
Enshadowed <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 933<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/14/01 11:01:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level for dragon raids?</span><hr size=1> 45 is about the minimum.  Get your FR/CR and MR up to a minimum of 100 UNbuffed.  Go heavier on MR till you hit 50 then start going more FR/CR since you won't be feared as much when you are 50+. <p><table>
<tr>
<td><a href="http://members.aol.com/mysticdominion/jaradisart.jpg" border=0><img src="http://members.aol.com/mysticdominion/jaradisartsmall.jpg"></a></td>

<td><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=View&Profile=0&Id=60309">Jaradis Stormcaller</a> - 54th Mystic - (Kael Faction)<br>
Twiggie Tymberwolf - 52rd Retired Wanderer - (Thurgadin/Skyshrine Faction)<br></td>
</tr>
</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uveldanlionsfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veldan Lionsfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/15/01 6:35:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level for dragon raids?</span><hr size=1> The cap is 250 on resists if I recall correctly.<br>
<br>
I completely disagree with the peole who say you need to be 47+ to get on a dragon raid.  I agree with their arguments, but just disagree on principle. (I'm a stubborn jacka$$ at times)  As long as you're in your 40's try and get your resist gear together. When you have your gear together (doesn't matter a what level) start signing up.  Who knows, you may get picked.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 890<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/15/01 11:20:57 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://216.242.60.166/chicktourney_com/larges/415.jpg width=110 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level for dragon raids?</span><hr size=1> -low 40s people don't have enough HPs to withstand a dragon for as long as a high 40s or low 50s.<br>
-resist rates are (resist stat) and level dependant.  you will constantly be feared without the right level, making you useless to the raid.<br>
-Vox and Naggy are level 55, so you can barely cast spells on him if you are as &quot;low&quot; as 49.  Anything lower shouldn't even try to cast on him. <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>58 Halfling Shaman
<br><img src=http://www.tbp.mb.ca/~stimpy/everquest/JuujuuHalflingSentry.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueoralsolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EoralSolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/15/01 12:43:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level for dragon raids?</span><hr size=1> As for the Kunark Dragons, AoE Fear can be a serious challenge.  I recommend at least 55 for Serv for example, as lower leveled people even with High Buffed MR above 150(Serv does NOT dispell) are still Feared/Stunned 90% of the time, making Melee and Casting insignificant.<br>
<br>
Eoral Slois <br>
Evoluxa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/15/01 1:18:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Level for dragon raids?</span><hr size=1> Naggi/Vox low to mid 40's IMO. I did Vox successfully at 43 without dying and being Feared only a couple of times. There was a 50 there that got feared more than I did. I made special note, however to get my resists up pretty good with gear. It should be noted, however, that at the end of the battle I was one scratch away from death. To me, A Palli, that is invigorating.<br>
<br>
Casters' level needs to be a bit higher. The main exception to this is Necros who can feed Mana if their spells do not stick. I spell sticking is alot more level dependant that getiing a good slab of steel to penatrate the flesh.<br>
<br>
I should also note here that I have been reaching over the normal minimum for combat since level 3. I went to the Crossroads in Butcher Block at 3 and then came back at 4.<br>
I was soloing the Gobbie camps at 5 or 6. I soloed Curflunk at 9. I admit that at 43 I probably was at the base minimum for doing Vox and a level or two lower than most tanks probably should be. <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglesig.jpg" border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1602.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1601.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.threadControl?topicID=1606.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1606.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1606.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (